Author: jl777c#5810
Content: if realtime monitors were installed in all the active miners' systems and reported to a central location, then you could get an accurate overall nethash

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: but I think there would be some objections to this

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: the pool can get a pretty good estimate of the realtime hashrate based on the sum of each workers results

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: the sum of all pools realtime hashrate is therefore knowable and it is consistently above the 120 block average hashrate that is the Msols, when the estimated solo mining is added. I have a feeling it isnt a 1:1 and that it takes more hashrate to get the 120 block average to register it

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: this is likely approx a 10% increased cost over what the instantaneous estimate would create

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: not sure why

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: tl:dr it likely costs 10% more to mine PIRATE than any Msols based estimate would calculate
